article.headline: N. Carolina A&amp,T 61, Bethune-Cookman 56
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Ed Jones and Nicholas Wilson scored 15 points each in North Carolina A&T's 61-56 win over Bethune-Cookman on Monday night. North Carolina A&T (11-13, 5-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) trailed 30-26 at halftime before tying the game, 39-39 with 11:50 to go. The Aggies then went on a 15-8 run, taking a 54-47 lead with 3:52 left in the game. The Wildcats brought the deficit to four twice in the final minute but couldn't pull any closer. Bethune-Cookman shot just 35.8 percent from the field (21 of 57), snapping a four-game road winning streak in conference play. The win was the fourth straight for the Aggies. C.J. Reed scored 12 points for the Wildcats and Jarrell Thomas and Tobias Mahone added 11 and 10 points, respectively.
